IIC_Control  (&240)
#Parent IIC_
{f25}Þ{f}	R0 =	device address, (bit 0 set to read, clear to write)
	R1 =	pointer to block
	R2 =	size of block (bytes)
#Line
Reads from or writes to the specified IIC device ({/}eg.{/} the clock chip and IIC compatible devices on podules).

Possible errors include 'No acknowledge from IIC device' and 'IIC system busy' if reentered.
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 944=>PRM-1:944>.
